# Sheet render (layout builder)

Read `.cursor/AGENTS.md` and `skills/generate-sheet-json/SKILL.md` before generating or editing JSON.

## JSON rules

- **Required**: `type` ("sheet" | "sheet-trigger" | "sheet-content" | "sheet-header" | "sheet-title" | "sheet-description" | "sheet-footer"), `id` (unique string).
- **Discriminant**: `type` must match exactly one of the registered values above.
- **BaseLayoutItem**: optional `className`, `style`, `condition`, `locked`.
- **Condition**: evaluated against `LayoutBuilder` `data` (see `lib/utils.ts`).
- **Children**: `children` is an array of layout items; nest valid `LayoutBuilderItem` objects.

## Renderer rules

- Map props to `@workspace/ui` components; do not add JSON fields without updating `types.ts`.
- Keep renderer in sync with `types.ts` — schema is the source of truth.

## Validation checklist

```
- [ ] type is one of: sheet, sheet-trigger, sheet-content, sheet-header, sheet-title, sheet-description, sheet-footer
- [ ] id is unique within the layout tree
- [ ] JSON is strict (no comments, no trailing commas)
- [ ] Props match types.ts (no invented fields)
```
